'''GNOME Do''' (also known as simply '''Do''') is a popular [[Free and open source software|free]] [[application launcher]] for [[Linux]] by [[David Siegel]] <ref>[http://lifehacker.com/software/featured-linux-download/fast-file-and-program-launching-with-gnome-do-330110.php Lifehacker - Fast File and Program Launching with GNOME Do]</ref>. Unlike other application launchers, it not only allows you to search for applications and files but it also allows you to specify actions to perform on search results by providing instantaneous, action-oriented search results that adapt to reflect user habits and preferences.
While it is designed primarily for the [[GNOME]] desktop, it works in other [[desktop environments]], such as [[KDE]].
